# verify/engine_boot.py and verify/rebench.py are THEMSELVES tests — they boot a
# real vLLM engine and time the patched kernel on a GPU. They are executable
# acceptance criteria (AC1 / AC3), run on hardware, and their results are
# recorded in RESULTS.md. Unit-testing them against fakes would test the fakes.
# Everything they depend on (backend_patch, the kernel, the reference) IS covered.
[run]
omit =
    verify/engine_boot.py
    verify/rebench.py
